# Ethical AI Fairness and Explainability Project

## Project Overview
This project analyzes fairness and explainability in a machine learning classification model using the Adult Income dataset. The model predicts whether a person earns more than $50K per year.

## Dataset
The Adult Income dataset was used. The sensitive attribute selected for fairness analysis was sex.

## Methods Used
- Data preprocessing
- Logistic Regression classification
- Model evaluation using accuracy, confusion matrix, and classification report
- Fairness analysis using Fairlearn
- Explainability analysis using SHAP and LIME

## Libraries
- pandas
- numpy
- scikit-learn
- fairlearn
- shap
- lime
- matplotlib

## How to Run
1. Open the notebook in Google Colab.
2. Run the installation cell.
3. Run all cells from top to bottom.
4. Review the model evaluation, fairness metrics, SHAP plots, and LIME explanation.

## Key Findings
The model performance was evaluated using standard classification metrics. Fairness metrics showed how model outcomes differed across sensitive groups. Explainability tools helped identify which features influenced predictions.

